@Helen Wright 

My wife is a huge football fan, and all she can think of when Maradona is mentioned is the 1986 hand of god thing.

I have a different gripe with him - Poland's most prolific sports commentator for many decades, Dariusz Szpakowski - a horribly annoying man, for whose carreer I have no rational explanation - had a mannerism of always mentioning Maradona by his full name. During any game that featured Maradona, Szpakowski shouted DIEGO ARMANDO MARADONA time after time after time. I wanted to reach into the TV and gag the guy. I can actually feel the anger stir in me at the memory alone, after all those years.

@Andrzej 
I would have the same feelings. I think what shocks the (football loving ones anyway) UK so much was his countrymen were so proud of the blatant cheating. To liken it to some kind of ‘miracle’ is the last straw. 
Amazing what a daily crossword puzzle can dredge up. I need extra cups of tea to calm down.

@Helen Wright 

IMDb lists two versions of the song under its entry for “Alfie” — one by Cilla Black and one by Cher. 

